title: Object Lessons by Anna Quindlen -EPUB (Perseu)
description:
It is the 1960s, in suburban New York
City. Maggie and her family, are in the
thrall of her powerful grandfather Jack
Scanlan. In the summer of her twelfth year,
Maggie is despertately trying to master the
object lessons her grandfather fills her
head with. But there is too much going on to
concentrate. Everything at home is in upheaval,
her grandfather is changing, and Maggie is
unsure if what she wants is worth having....
